      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 725: Recovery is only attempted when lastCommitId() returns empty, but a missing object deeper in history or in HEAD\u0027s tree can leave HEAD readable and make lastCommitId() non-empty. The new validate() explicitly detects those cases, yet fetch/merge will still continue into the old retry loop because validation is not run on fetch/merge failure paths. Trigger repository validation when git operations fail due to object lookup/read errors, not only when lastCommitId() is empty, and schedule recovery on invalid repositories there as well.",
