      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 3938: validate() can be very expensive because it walks every commit and tree reachable from HEAD while holding opMtx_. A large conversation history will block all repository mutations and fetch/merge work for the duration of a full object graph scan. Since recovery is only needed after an operation failure, consider using libgit2\u0027s object walk/fsck-style validation only on the failing path with bounded logging, or short-circuit based on the exact missing object error when available.",
      "revId": "3ce9e4bac4a0cd6f4800b5f0df659f76f5be25f6",
